@startuml c4-pipeline
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #DDEEFF
    BorderColor #336699
    FontColor #111111
    ArrowColor #336699
}

skinparam partition {
    BackgroundColor #F0F4FF
    BorderColor #336699
    FontColor #222222
}

skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
    BorderColor #F9A825
}

title CI/CD/CD Pipeline - Digital Therapy Assistant\n(Stage-Gate Pattern with GitHub Actions)

|#E8F5E9| GitHub (Trigger) |
start
:Developer pushes commit or opens PR\nto **main** or **develop** branch;
note right: Trigger:\ngit push / PR open\n→ github.com/org/dta

|#DDEEFF| CI Workflow\n(ci.yml) |
:**GATE: Build**\nCompile Java source with Maven\nFail fast on compilation errors;
note right: mvn compile\nFails pipeline if compile errors

fork
    :**Unit Tests**\nmvn test (JUnit 5)\nComponent-level isolation;
fork again
    :**Integration Tests**\nmvn verify (Spring Boot Test)\nFull context + H2 in-memory DB;
fork again
    :**Code Quality**\nSonarQube / Checkstyle\nCoverage threshold ≥ 80%;
fork again
    :**Dependency Check**\nOWASP dependency-check\nFlag CVE vulnerabilities;
fork again
    :**Security Scan**\nTrivy filesystem scan\nBlock on HIGH/CRITICAL CVEs;
end fork

note right: All five checks run in **parallel**.\nAny failure blocks the pipeline here.

:**GATE: CI Passed**\nAll parallel checks green → proceed;
note right: PR cannot be merged\nuntil this gate passes.

|#FFF8E1| CD Build Workflow\n(cd-build.yml) |
note left: Trigger: push to **main** only\n(after PR merge / direct push)

:**Build Docker Images**\n`docker build` frontend (Nginx+React)\n`docker build` backend (Spring Boot JAR);

:**Push to Registry**\n`docker push ghcr.io/org/dta-frontend:<sha>`\n`docker push ghcr.io/org/dta-backend:<sha>`;
note right: Tagged with:\n- git SHA (immutable)\n- `latest` (floating)

:**Smoke Test**\nPull built images in CI runner\nStart containers with `docker compose up -d`\nHIT /actuator/health — expect HTTP 200;
note right: Verifies images are runnable\nbefore touching production.

:**GATE: Images Verified**\nSmoke test passes → proceed to deploy;

|#FCE4EC| CD Deploy Workflow\n(cd-deploy.yml) |
note left: Trigger: image gate passed\n(sequential, not parallel)

:**Deploy to EC2**\nSSH into EC2 Elastic IP\n`docker compose pull`\n`docker compose up -d --remove-orphans`;
note right: Uses GitHub Secret:\nEC2_SSH_KEY, EC2_HOST\nZero-downtime rolling restart

:⏱**Wait for Startup**\nSleep 20 s — allow containers\nto initialise and bind ports;

fork
    :**Frontend Check**\ncurl http://EC2:3000/\nExpect HTTP 200;
fork again
    :⚙️ **Backend Health Check**\ncurl http://EC2:8080/actuator/health\nExpect {status:"UP"};
end fork

:**GATE: Post-Deployment Verification**\nBoth checks pass → deployment successful;

|#E8F5E9| GitHub (Notify) |
if (All gates passed?) then (yes)
    :**Deployment Complete**\nGitHub Actions status: success\nCommit SHA deployed to EC2;
    :Optional: post success summary\nto PR comment or Slack channel;
else (no — any gate failed)
    :**Pipeline Blocked**\nGitHub Actions status: failure\nPrevious stable image remains running on EC2;
    :Notify team via\nGitHub Actions alert / email;
endif

stop

legend right
    |= Symbol |= Meaning |
    | GATE | Stage boundary — failure blocks downstream |
    | fork...end fork | Parallel execution |
    | | Security-related step |
    | | Docker operation |
endlegend

@enduml
